We have created a "bare-bones" URL shortening web-based service which has served well as a early sample project.

We now would like to expand this with additional, more advanced, functionality.

This enhanced version is being fleshed out into a whole new product (it was previously only internal, and had no official name, but rather a kind of 'codename' of "MWlink". The new name will be "Go2My.Link" (or with a GitHub Repo name of "Go2My.Link"). This is a product of MWBM Partners Ltd (under the trading name of MWservices), and will thus be under our organisation GitHub account GitHub.com/MWBMPartners)

The Key of the basis/idea behind the new expanded webservice is a URL shortening service/website where a user can enter a URL, and have a short-url (short link) produced, in a similar way to Bit.ly.

The app is to consist of the following:

A) Main website/domain (using Bitly as an example, Bitly.com) for promotion/sign-up and quickly generating shortlink URLs. The "Face" of the new web service.
B) Second website/domain name  (using Bitly as an example, Bit.ly) as the default domain for short links
C) Third domain/website to provide a service similar to LinkTree, where a list of SOME defined links are listed on a single page. Useful for linking to across social media (we'll refer to this element of the service as LinksPage)
C) API for generation of shortlinks using API Keys
	Generation of Short link URLs in item A (whether by a logged in user or 'anonymous'/guest should use the same API in the background for generating shortlink URLS).

As noted above, we alreay have a somewhat basic implementation of this. This early version uses a MySQL backend database (i can attach a databse copy), but i want to expand and enhanced this as detailed below:

