Please use the following technologies for development of the entire 'Portal' project
* PHP (minimum PHP 8.5 for longevity - current as of November 2025 - but with backward compatibility for PHP 8.4 as well (via conditional statements etc) where necessary.
	* PHP code should
		* Use PHP Predefined Constants wherever possible to aid with host platform neutrality (ie, use DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR instead of '/' in paths, PHP_EOL etc)
		* Full notation for code blocks such as (but not limited to) IF statements, no shortened notation
		* source code should be indented appropriately (upon deployment, code CAN be minified to conserve bandiwidth, but from a dev point everything MUST be easy to read and follow, so indentation is extremely important) with detailed inline comments/annotations to assith with code readibility, understanding, debugging and future learning/maintenance of code
			* Comments can/should provide links to external (preferrably official) documentation for further guidance. 
		* A modular development structure
		* Minimise code duplication but grouping shared code and reusing/reaccessing them via PHP REQUIRE, REQUIRE_ONCE, INCLUDE & INCLUDE_ONCE
		
		  appropriate checks and error handling for REQUIRED and INCLUDED components should be done to avoid errors should files not exist/not be retrievable
		* Provide "switches" (perhaps via URL Parameters or other means) to enable detailed PHP error visiblity by use of a URL Param such as &debug=true (for dev purposes only)
