*API*
------------------------
Secure API (utilising API Keys/CSRF and other security standard mechanisms) must also be supported, with the following functionality

* Create Short URL
* Modify Short URL
* Disable Existing Short URL
* Access Analytics info

API should have the capability to return data in the following formats:
* JSON (default)
* XML (very structured with embedded XSLT for easier view in browser)

API can also be used to create a companion mobile app or managing your short URLs and user acounts.

As with the main components of the app, we do not want to expose that we use PHP for the backend workings of the API, as such API endpoints should not be link create.php. Instead maybe have the actual API endpoint processing in a index.php within a create subdirectory (for example).

